  "match": {
    "name_regex": "(?i)soundcore Liberty 4 Pro",
    "service_uuids_any": [
      "0cf12d31-fac3-4553-bd80-d6832e7b3954"
    ]
  },
  "channels": {
    "rfcomm-main": {
      "transport": "rfcomm",
      "uuid": "0cf12d31-fac3-4553-bd80-d6832e7b3954",
      "secure": false,
      "protocol": {
        "framing": "soundcore_v1",
        "_doc": "Identical framing to the Space One Pro. host->device: 08 ee 00 00 00 <cmd:2> <len:2 LE total> <payload..> <crc>. device->host: 09 ff 00 00 01 <cmd:2> <len:2 LE> <payload..> <crc>. crc = sum(prev)&0xff. Command bytes equal OpenSCQ30 Command([hi,lo]).",
        "cmd_prefix": "08ee000000",
        "resp_prefix": "09ff000001",
        "checksum": "sum8"
      }
    }
  },
  "default_channel": "rfcomm-main",
  "platforms": {
    "pixelos": {
      "detect": {
        "manufacturer": "Google",
        "system_prop": {
          "ro.product.brand": "google"
        }
      },
      "requires": [
        "root",
        "lsposed",
        "pkg:com.android.systemui",
        "pkg:com.android.settings"
      ],
      "inject": {
        "settings_pkg": "com.android.settings",
        "systemui_pkg": "com.android.systemui",
        "about_fragment": "com.android.settings.bluetooth.BluetoothDetailsConfigurableFragment",
        "surfaces": [
          "device_details",
          "volume_panel"
        ],
        "reserved_ids": {
          "anc": 1001
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "_capabilities_source": "Capability list mirrors OpenSCQ30's closest TWS cousins Liberty 5 (A3957)/Liberty 4 NC (A3947), then VERIFIED live 2026-06-14 by driving the Soundcore app + btsnoop (RFCOMM, payload in tshark data.data, Liberty ACL handle 0x000d). Confirmed: wearing_detection 0181, sound_leak_compensation 109a (NOT 1086), low_battery_prompt 1082, multipoint 0b84, ldac SET 01ff (NOT 017f; reboots device). sound_mode 0681 uses an adaptive 5-byte payload `<B0><B1>00<wind>ff` (B0 00=adaptive-ANC/01=manual/03=airplane) — different from the over-ear; discrete mode mapping still needs re-capture. Aux: 2003 = real-time volume-meter read. Still _verified:false (guessed): anc_cycle 0682, gaming_mode 0187, touch_tone 0183, wearing_tone 018c, limit_high_volume 2082, auto_power_off 0186, eq 0281, button 0481.",
  "functions": [
    {
      "id": "sound_mode",
      "type": "multitoggle",
      "title": "Noise control",
      "title_i18n": {
        "ru": "Управление шумом"
      },
      "capability": "sound_modes",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "anc",
          "label": "Noise Cancelling",
          "icon": "anc",
          "label_i18n": {
            "ru": "Шумоподавление"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "off",
          "label": "Off",
          "icon": "off",
          "label_i18n": {
            "ru": "Выкл."
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "transparency",
          "label": "Transparency",
          "icon": "transparency",
          "label_i18n": {
            "ru": "Прозрачность"
          }
        }
      ],
      "set": {
        "command": "0681",
        "payload_template": "{mode}5000000005",
        "option_values": {
          "anc": "00",
          "off": "01",
          "transparency": "02"
        },
        "_capture_2026-06-14": "The official app uses a DIFFERENT (adaptive) 0681 payload than the over-ear: 5 bytes `<B0><B1>00<B3 wind>ff`. Captured B0: 00=ambient/adaptive-ANC, 01=manual-ANC (B1=level 1-10, 0b=adaptive), 03=airplane mode; B3=wind/'Air protection' (01/00). Our 6-byte `{mode}5000000005` template differs but switched modes OK in the 2026-06-01 test. The discrete anc/off/transparency mapping below is UNCONFIRMED against the app (which exposes an ANC↔Transparency slider, not 3 buttons) — likely has the same off/transparency swap the over-ear had; re-verify before trusting."
      },
      "read": {
        "command": "0101",
        "response_command": "0101",
        "state_byte_index": 134,
        "value_map": {
          "00": "anc",
          "01": "off",
          "02": "transparency"
        }
      },
      "inject": "auto",
      "ui": {
        "setting_id": 1001,
        "surfaces": [
          "device_details",
          "volume_panel"
        ]
      },
      "_verified": true,
      "_verified_note": "ANC=00 confirmed; full mode mapping needs re-capture (see _capture note). state byte idx134 flips."
    },
